%S A396873 0,0,0,4,15308,8579618,2991239343
%N A396873 Number of relations on an n-set whose minimum-deletion-to-transitivity equals three.
%C A396873 a(n) counts binary relations R on {1,...,n} such that R is not transitive, no single-pair deletion from R yields a transitive relation, no two-pair deletion from R yields a transitive relation, but there exist three ordered pairs p, q, r in R with R \ {p,q,r} transitive. That is, the minimum number of single-pair deletions required to make R transitive equals 3.
%C A396873 Equivalently, the minimum vertex cover of the conflict graph on R (vertices = ordered pairs in R; edges join (a,b) and (b,c) whenever (a,c) is not in R) has size 3.
%e A396873 For n=3 the a(3)=4 relations are obtained from the complete antireflexive tournament R0 = {(1,2),(2,1),(1,3),(3,1),(2,3),(3,2)} by adjoining any subset of the three loops (1,1),(2,2),(3,3) of size 0 or 1. Deleting any single pair from R0 leaves five pairs  that still violate transitivity; deleting any two leaves three  pairs that still violate transitivity; deleting three suitably chosen pairs (e.g. (2,1),(3,1),(3,2)) yields the transitive relation {(1,2),(1,3),(2,3)}. Adjoining two or three reflexive pairs would reduce the minimum to 2.
%Y A396873 Cf. A006905, A396664, A396669.
